minimal arch linux desktop dotfiles

this repository contains a direct hyprland setup with kitty, zsh, waybar,
rofi, dunst, and optional desktop helpers.

quick setup

    git clone <repository-url> ~/Dev/dotfiles
    cd ~/Dev/dotfiles
    ./install.sh --dry-run
    ./install.sh

the installer:

    shows required and optional package groups
    asks before running pacman
    backs up conflicting files
    creates symlinks into xdg config paths
    creates a local monitor override
    verifies files before reloading hyprland

package groups

    core
        hyprland kitty zsh uwsm fzf eza
    desktop
        waybar rofi dunst
    optional/bluetooth
        blueman network-manager-applet
    optional/clipboard
        wl-clipboard cliphist
    optional/power
        wlogout
    optional/screenshots
        grim slurp satty

repository layout

    config/    xdg configuration files
    bin/       executable helper scripts
    packages/  pacman package groups
    local/     machine-specific examples
    scripts/   installer, linker, verifier, and restore commands

machine-specific monitor settings

copy local/hypr/local.conf.example to ~/.config/hypr/local.conf and add
monitor rules for the machine. this file is never symlinked or tracked.

updates

    cd ~/Dev/dotfiles
    git pull
    ./scripts/verify.sh repository
    ./install.sh

rollback

backups are stored under:

    ~/.local/state/dotfiles/backups/

restore a backup with:

    ./scripts/restore.sh ~/.local/state/dotfiles/backups/<timestamp>

the installer does not log out, reboot, or stop unrelated processes.
